      Hard choices. Yes we need jobs, but they need to be sustainable.  Walmart is gonna pay a buck or so above minimum wage and very few of these 1,200 new employees will be able to afford the company's health insurance. A year after they open if 20% of employees are on the company's healthcare plan, I'll be shocked.  So explain to me how this really helps DC? We do get sales and property tax revenues but those are partially or fully offset by other negative impacts.   <br />
